HEADWORD: Timepleaser
<hw>Time"pleas`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who complies
with prevailing opinions, whatever they may be; a timeserver.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Timepleasers</qex>, flatterers, foes to nobleness.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Time policy</ent>⟦br⟧
